dc_title_s: United States National Transportation Atlas Interstate Highways, 2008
dc_description_s: This line shapefile represents rural and urban interstate highways. U.S. National Transportation Atlas Interstate Highways is part of the National Highway Planning Network, published by the Federal Highway Administration as part of the National Transportation Atlas Databases for the United States. This layer is part of the 2014 ESRI Data and Maps collection for ArcGIS 10.2. U.S. National Transportation Atlas Interstate Highways provides a comprehensive database of interstate highways from the nation's principal arterial highway system and the National Highway System. The data is generalized to improve draw performance and be used effectively at a national level. ESRI and U.S. Bureau of Transportation Statistics. (2014). United States National Transportation Atlas Interstate Highways, 2008. ESRI. Available at: http://purl.stanford.edu/qn309jc5979
dc_creator_sm: United States. Bureau of Transportation Statistics
